superSourceDescription: The European Chemicals Agency (ECHA) develops and maintains chemical dossiers in their International Uniform Chemical Information Database (IUCLID). The IUCLID provides a platform to record, store, maintain and exchange data on intrinsic and hazard properties of chemical substances, such as toxicity effect(s) and dose-response data. While non-cancer and cancer human health toxicity values are not necessarily provided in IUCLID chemical dossiers, important dose-response information such as No-Observed-Adverse-Effect-Levels (NOAELs) and/or Lowest-Observed-Adverse-Effect-Levels (LOAELs) are listed when and where available from human or experimental animal studies. (For more information see: https://echa.europa.eu/).
